Like people are saying in the comments, `Double`s don&#39;t actually *store* a specific number of trailing zeroes - *1.230000000000* and *1.23* are stored the same way. Even if you specify a certain number of zeroes, that info is lost.

If you need to store those numbers with an arbitrary number of trailing zeroes, you should probably store them as `String`s - that way they&#39;ll display correctly when you print them. Just convert them to `Double`s when you want to actually use them as numbers

````
