You messed up your configuration.

**maven-compiler-plugin** is responsible for compiling your project.
It&#39;s configuration does not take `mainClass` element. Good IDE should highlight this as an error (IntelliJ does)

**maven-exec-plugin** can launch java apps. It needs exec.mainClass argument, but you didn&#39;t pass it.
See https://www.baeldung.com/maven-java-main-method:
```lang-xml
&lt;build&gt;
    &lt;plugins&gt;
        &lt;plugin&gt;
            &lt;groupId&gt;org.codehaus.mojo&lt;/groupId&gt;
            &lt;artifactId&gt;exec-maven-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;
            &lt;version&gt;3.0.0&lt;/version&gt;
            &lt;configuration&gt;
                &lt;mainClass&gt;com.baeldung.main.Exec&lt;/mainClass&gt;
            &lt;/configuration&gt;
        &lt;/plugin&gt;
    &lt;/plugins&gt;
&lt;/build&gt;
```

**spring-boot-maven-plugin** has a lot of tools specifically tailored for Spring boot apps. It has its own goal for launching Spring apps:
```
mvn spring-boot:run
```

IMHO you will be better off if you rely on this plugin to launch your app (on dev machine)

